For sale is a 6.5 x 55 caliber Swedish Mauser.  This is an M96/38 from the very desirable Oberndorfer facility.  Has the 24 inch barrel instead of the nice, but more unwieldy 29 inch barrels in the M96's.  Following parts are numbers matching: Butt plate, receiver, all bolt and safety parts, front barrel band. All firearms sales are final and considered “AS IS” unless warranty is otherwise stated. We will ship weapons to any FFL in the continental United States for a flat rate fee of $20 for handguns and $30 for long guns. We will not ship firearms to individuals. A valid, signed copy of an FFL must be presented before firearms are released for shipment. Precision Firearms only ships ammunition via UPS with varying fees depending upon the weight, call or email for pricing. All other products will ship via United States Postal Service unless otherwise requested with fees varying from $5.70 - $11.70 depending on size and weight of product.

Return Policy
Incorrect items: If a product is not the product that you ordered, Precision Firearms will either replace the product or give you a full refund if returned within 10 days of receipt. Precision Firearms cannot replace products that have been used, unless they are covered under the manufacturer's warranty, you will send these items directly to the manufacturer for replacement. Note: We do not accept returns on ammunition, scopes, binoculars, flashlights, software, DVD’s or hearing protectors. Special Order Items may not be returned.
Firearms are non-returnable and non-refundable. However, to insure your satisfaction with your new firearm, we do offer help in getting the firearm covered under the manufacturer’s warranty, terms and conditions of each individual manufacturer apply. Precision Firearms is not responsible for warranting firearms. 
Manufacturer Warranty & Service: In some cases, it may be best to send your firearm directly to the manufacturer for repair or adjustment. Some manufacturers offer superior service and we may direct you in this regard, depending on the brand. 

Used Gun Purchase (Buy Back): At our discretion, we may offer to buy a firearm, at a price to be determined by Precision Firearms.

Electronic Devices, Hearing Protectors, Lasers, Rangefinders, Lights and other electronic devices are covered by the manufacturer, and must be returned to the manufacturer for repair or replacement. 
No refunds or returns are accepted on these types of items. We only carry Electronic Devices that are covered under warranty by a reputable manufacturer.
Please consult your owner’s manual for warranty information, or call us for instructions.

If you are not satisfied with your Accessory Product (other than exceptions such as firearms, electronic devices, optics etc.), you may return it within 10 days for a full refund, less shipping costs (and fees) and restocking fees (20% minimum restocking fee*). Item must be unused and in 100% original condition with all labels and papers intact. You must have a 'Return Authorization Number' (RMA) before returning the item. Contact us by phone or email for an RMA- BEFORE YOU RETURN THE PRODUCT! Accessories include (but are not limited to): Holsters, Belts, Knives, Cleaning Supplies, and Firearm Add-Ons. *Restocking fees: All returns will be charge a twenty percent restocking fee. Left Handed Items are special order items, and are not returnable. Left Handed Orders May Not Be Cancelled.

The Parker-Hale .451 Reproduction Whitworth percussion rifle is in good condition with
minor dings and dents in the wood, tool marks on the barrel bands and a minor scratch on top of the breech.

This gun can be shot out your bedroom window, crack the skull of a coon and never wake a soul. True "urban" rifle if you like taking out stuff but live close to town. No joke, a red rider makes more noise then this thing. A picture of some types of rounds I have are included next to a 9mm bullet. Comes with an air take. Can service the rifle about 40 times and each service gives about 20 shots. Comes with soft case. Magazine holds 8 pellets and this thing is a bolt action air rifle. Will consider trades but would prefer to sell. Check out www.youtube.com/watch?v=OUEwxg32s6Y. This is a video of a guy using the same gun I have but stock kill a hog! This is my baby but my its Xmas time and need to free up some cash.

title: For Sale:  Hammerli (SIG) 212  w/box
postcontent:
The Hammerli 212 is the shorter (5") barrel derivative of the legendary 208, the gun never bettered for competition accuracy.  The 212 is the field version, for sports use but also popular in Europe for intelligence agency use.  Accuracy is comparable to the 208.  As accurate as the 208 (and better than any USA handgun) at 25 yards, with a little fall-off at 50-75 yards due to the barrel length but less first shot inaccuracy than the 208.   Gun accuracy is at the 0.2MOA level.  The accuracy and handling of these guns is far superior to the best S&W41 or CT-based High Standard Victors.

Rear sights are very low profile, adjustable for windage only.  Suitable (and in Europe, used for) concealed carry.  Elevation-adjustable low-profile rear sight can be mounted, by skilled gunsmiths.

Supplied with the 50 gram barrel weight.  A scope rail that also can hold dot or doctor sights can be attached to the weight dovetail.

Adjustable trigger pull, from about 5 oz to 3 lbs.  

Standard velocity ammunition only.  Provided with one magazine, up to 3 additional available.

All federal and state laws observed for sale or transfer.  No sales considered that do not follow those laws strictly, including for law enforcement officer sales.

Mfr listed as Sig Sauer, but it actually is made by Hammerli - SIG before Sauer acquired the SIG handgun production, later sold to Blaser.

The original design probably was by Reising (USA) further developed by Walther (Germany), with the patents purchased by Hammerli after WWII and vastly improved by them, with further improvements in the trigger by SIG in the 1970s.

title: For Sale:   KIMBER MODEL 82 GOVT HEAVY TARGET RIFLE
postcontent:
THIS IS A VERY NICE HIGHLY DESIRED DARK WALNUT KIMBER MODEL 82 GOVT RIFLE 

Not NIB rifle, was bought with 3 others in July this year and it has been shot maybe 200 rounds through the bore. I tried it out with the Iron Sights and it did well, considering it was my first attempt at shooting peep sights. It was my plan to keep one Kimber for glass and one for iron, but decided after shooting the iron that I preferred using a scope. In addition to this reason, I just bought a Winchester 52D and with a H&R Model 12 I dont need two kimbers. I have sold two of these in the last month and half for $700.

Rifle includes everything that came with it from CMP (Rifle, Front and Rear sights, authentication letter, inspection certificate, packing box and shipping box)

(This is not a Star Grade rifle)

On inspection, this rifle has all the parts and the rifle itself. Considering the way these were handled in the 90’s under inventory control.  This rifle I am selling is in good condition with slight bumps and indentions done I assume during inventory and being moved around on the racks at CMP that are easily taken out with wet towel and hot iron. I was going to take out the bumps, but realized to do it properly I need to strip the rifle of its finish and then steam out the bumps and refinish. Which I did not want to do at this time. 

Bolt and Rifle serial number match USGM010xxx.

I purchased several of these rifles in August and the first one I used was a good shooter USGM001xxx, so I am going to sell the rest of them. 

All I have done to my personal shooter is trigger adjustment, Recrown barrel, and lap the bore. These are very good shooters for the money. If you dont know of the rifle you can read about them on Rimfire Central Forums or all over the internet.

I will transfer the rifles at this point, one of three ways. 
I will ship to your FFL dealer if they will receive from an individual for actual shipping cost. If not then I will have the rifle shipped through my local FFL dealer. The fee depends on how much he charges me. 
I can legally ship person to person using USPS within the state of Florida ONLY.  Buyer is responsible for all shipping cost. Cost within the state is $34 insured and priority 2nd Day.
Or I will do a FTF transfer in Sebastian, Florida.
***********************************************************
Some information in regards to the Kimber Model 82 Government Rifle:
http://www.odcmp.com/Sales/kimber82desc.htm

**************Added note: The factory trigger with no modifications can be adjusted to as low as 13oz. If you have a gunsmith disassemble, add the available replacement trigger spring and hone and polish both the trigger foot and sear. The trigger can go down as far as 7oz I believe. The one I shoot is 10oz with replacement trigger spring. The receiver is dovetailed to accept a 11mm ring set scope*****************
